    6086/   860D8 :                     ; the Galois method and a sample of 65536 bytes produced gives the following values.
    6087/   860D8 :                     
 AS V1.42 Beta [Bld 278] - Source File basic68k.asm - Page 106 - 5/14/2026 21:6:22


    6088/   860D8 :                     ; Entropy = 7.997442 bits per byte
    6089/   860D8 :                     ; Optimum compression would reduce these 65536 bytes by 0 percent
    6090/   860D8 :                     
    6091/   860D8 :                     ; Chi square distribution for 65536 samples is 232.01, and
    6092/   860D8 :                     ; randomly would exceed this value 75.00 percent of the time
    6093/   860D8 :                     
    6094/   860D8 :                     ; Arithmetic mean value of data bytes is 127.6724, 127.5 would be random
    6095/   860D8 :                     ; Monte Carlo value for Pi is 3.122871269, error 0.60 percent
    6096/   860D8 :                     ; Serial correlation coefficient is -0.000370, totally uncorrelated would be 0.0
    6097/   860D8 :                     
